Subject: [PATCH] ALSA: hda - Always check array bounds in alc_get_line_out_pfx
Git-commit: 71aa5ebe36a4e936eff281b375a4707b6a8320f2
Patch-mainline: 3.7-rc2
References: FATE#314311

Even when CONFIG_SND_DEBUG is not enabled, we don't want to
return an arbitrary memory location when the channel count is
larger than we expected.

Cc: stable@kernel.org
Signed-off-by: David Henningsson <david.henningsson@canonical.com>
Signed-off-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>

